Air Quality Data Warehouse

This database stores Atmospheric, Gaseous Pollutant, Greenhouse Gas, and Particulate hourly historical and forecast data loaded into a PostgreSQL database hosted in Supabase.

The schema is normalized to approximately Third Normal Form by:
•	Separating entities into related tables
•	Avoiding repeated data
ER Diagram

Database Overview
This database contains five tables: 
•	Particulates & AQI 
•	Gaseous pollutants 
•	Atmospheric/radiation 
•	Daily Summary
Entry Relationship Summary
Table	Purpose
Particulates & AQI 	Air Quality Index and Particulate Matter metrics
Gaseous pollutants 	Gaseous pollutants and greenhouse gases metrics
Atmospheric/radiation 	Atmospheric metrics and radiation
Daily Summary	Bridge table connecting metrics

Table Documentation
1. Particulates & AQI
Purpose
Stores the daily and historical United States Air Quality Index and their descriptions as well as particulate matter standardized by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) from the Open-Meteo API. 
Example
AQI 125 = Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups
PM10 4 = Satisfactory Air Quality
Table Structure
Column Name	Data Type	Key	Description
Time	TIMESTAMP	Primary Key	Date and time of data entry 
pm10	NUMERIC(7, 2)   		EPA measurement
us_aqi          	SMALLINT		EPA measurement
us_aqi_category	aqi_category		Description of US AQI 


2. Gaseous_pollutants
